    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n**Refer to Strategy 1 and 3**\r\n\r\n1. Run the code and compare the output to the comments describing what should be happening. Take note of any unexpected behavior.\r\n2. *Discuss: With a partner, identify what might be causing the issue. Consider what is happening differently than expected.*\r\n2. Since there is no error message, use the chatbot on Level 4 to help analyze your code and find the bug. Ask for debugging advice or explanations of why the code isn't behaving as expected.\r\n3. Modify the code to fix the issue.\r\n\t- **Hint:** Focus on checking the logic of your code rather than just syntax errors!\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Unit Guide**\r\n\r\nDocument your experience with this debugging strategy:\r\n- What worked? \r\n- What challenges did you face? \r\n- How did this strategy help? \r\n- When might it be most useful in the future?",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\n# create two painter objects\nsusan = Painter()\njoe = Painter()\n\n# turn right by turning left 3x\n# takes an object name as the parameter\ndef turn_right(painter):\n  painter.turn_left()\n  painter.turn_left()\n  painter.turn_left()\n\n# paints a continuous line as it moves\ndef paint_line(painter):\n  painter.move()\n  painter.take_paint()\n  painter.paint(\"blue\")\n  painter.move()\n\n# object susan will paint the top horizontal grid line, from the first square to the last square\npaint_line(susan)\npaint_line(susan)\npaint_line(susan)\n\n# object joe will turn right and paint the left vertical grid line, from the first square to the last square\nturn_right(joe)\npaint_line(joe)\npaint_line(joe)\npaint_line(joe)\n\n# Expected outcome: the top line of the grid will be painted a solid blue line\n# Expected outcome: the left line of the grid will be painted a solid blue line\n\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      },
      "openFiles": [
        "0"
      ]
    },
